Step 1: Go to azure portal.

step 2: Search for policy.

step 3: Click on definitions on the left side.

step 4: Type require a tag and then click require a tag on resource.

step 5: Click on assign policy at the top.

step 6: Fill the required details under basics, parameters, etc and then click review and create. Now you can go to assignments under definitions to view your creation.

step 7: Now search for public ip address.

step 8: Click create and then fill the required details in basics.

step 9: Under tags, type CreatedBy : Jeremy Wallace.

step 10: Finally click on review and create.
